 phases. -->\n  <div class="andara-section">\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <h2>2. The Four Expressions of Water in Nature</h2>\n      <p>We’re taught that water has three phases: solid, liquid, vapor. In reality, there is a fourth expression that behaves differently at interfaces — often called “<a href="/science/water/structured-water">structured water</a>” or <a href="/science/water/ez-water">EZ-like water</a> (Exclusion Zone–like water).</p>\n      <ul>\n        <li><strong>Solid (Ice):</strong> Molecules locked into stable hexagonal arrangements. Holds shape, transmits patterns (snowflakes, crystal memory).</li>\n        <li><strong>Liquid (Bulk Water):</strong> Molecules in constant motion, forming and breaking hydrogen bonds. This is the everyday drinking, bathing, and river water we know.</li>\n        <li><strong>Vapor (Gas):</strong> Individual molecules drifting freely. Carries water information and charge into the air through humidity and clouds.</li>\n        <li><strong>Structured / EZ-like Water:</strong> Appears at interfaces — along hydrophilic surfaces, gels, membranes. Molecules packed more tightly, arranged in layers or hexagonal sheets. Shows altered properties: density, viscosity, charge separation.</li>\n      </ul>\n      <p class="andara-text-lead"><strong>Core message:</strong> Water is not one thing. It is a shape-shifter, constantly re-organizing itself between these phases. The inner structure in each phase decides how water stores energy, transports ions, and supports life.</p>\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--01 andara-grid--visual">\n        <!-- Visual for The Four Expressions of Water in Nature -->\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- AI LAYOUT PROMPT: Section explaining water organization. Visual: split graphic (chaotic vs. coherent dots). -->\n  <div class="andara-section">\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <h2>3. From Random Molecules to Coherent Fields</h2>\n      <p>In a glass, water looks uniform. But at the microscopic level, molecules are not randomly scattered — they form clusters, layers and domains that can be more or less ordered.</p>\n      <ul>\n        <li><strong>Hydrogen bonds:</strong> Each water molecule can connect to others like a tiny tetrahedral magnet. These connections constantly form and break on femto– to picosecond timescales. (<a href="/science/water/hydration-clusters">Learn more about hydration clusters</a>)</li>\n        <li><strong>Clusters & micro-domains:</strong> Areas where water molecules momentarily align into structures. These micro-structures affect viscosity, diffusion, and ion movement.</li>\n        <li><strong>Fields & coherence:</strong> Under certain conditions (<a href="/science/minerals/ionic-vs-colloidal">minerals</a>, light, surfaces, charge), water can shift from a chaotic pattern to a more coherent field. Coherent water behaves differently: it can hold charge, support proton conduction, and show more stable properties.</li>\n      </ul>\n      <p class="andara-text-lead"><strong>Key idea:</strong> The quality of water is not only what is dissolved in it, but how its molecules are structured.</p>\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--02 andara-grid--visual">\n        <!-- Visual for From Random Molecules to Coherent Fields -->\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- AI LAYOUT PROMPT: Section on water activation. Visual: 4-icon row (movement, minerals, light, fields) leading to "Activated" droplet. -->\n  <div class="andara-section">\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <h2>4. Activation – When Water Wakes Up</h2>\n      <p>In nature, water is rarely static. It flows, spins, rises, falls, meets rock, light and air. Each of these inputs acts like a tuning fork, nudging water into a more organized state.</p>\n      <p><strong>Four primary activators:</strong></p>\n      <ul>\n        <li><strong>Movement & <a href="/science/water/vortexing">Vortexing</a>:</strong> Spirals, vortices and turbulence continually rearrange water’s inner geometry. Natural rivers “knead” water into a more structured state compared to stagnant pools.</li>\n        <li><strong>Minerals & Ions:</strong> Dissolved ionic minerals (especially <a href="/science/water/sulfate-school">sulfates</a>, magnesium, calcium, silicates) provide charge carriers and scaffolding. They help water organize charge separation, enabling better conduction and structuring at interfaces.</li>\n        <li><strong>Light & Temperature Gradients:</strong> Sunlight, infrared, and thermal contrasts drive phase shifts and EZ-like formation. Light can feed water with photon energy, which gets stored as separation of charges.</li>\n        <li><strong>Electric & Magnetic Fields:</strong> Natural fields from Earth, lightning, Schumann resonances, and local charges influence ion distribution. This shapes where structured domains appear and how bioelectric processes unfold.</li>\n      </ul>\n      <p class="andara-text-lead"><strong>Key idea:</strong> “Activated water” is simply water that has been moved, mineralized, lit and charged into a more coherent, information-rich state — much closer to the water that nourishes mountain springs and living cells.</p>\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--04 andara-grid--visual">\n        <!-- Visual for Activation – When Water Wakes Up -->\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- AI LAYOUT PROMPT: Section on measurement. Visual: 4-column infographic for pH, ORP, EC, Turbidity. -->\n  <div class="andara-section">\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <h2>5. How We Measure What Eyes Can’t See</h2>\n      <p>To understand water as a terrain, we need parameters that describe its inner state. Four of the most useful are:</p>\n      <ul>\n        <li><strong><a href="/science/water/ph-orp-ec">pH</a> – Acid–Base Balance:</strong> Tells us about proton concentration. Slightly alkaline ranges in drinking water often correlate with more stable terrains.</li>\n        <li><strong><a href="/science/water/ph-orp-ec">ORP</a> (Oxidation–Reduction Potential):</strong> Measures water’s tendency to give or take electrons. Lower ORP often indicates more reducing, electron-rich environments.</li>\n        <li><strong><a href="/science/water/ph-orp-ec">EC</a> / Conductivity:</strong> Shows how well water conducts electrical current. Higher EC means more ions present – a more “wired” medium for charge movement.</li>\n        <li><strong><a href="/science/water/turbidity">Turbidity</a> / Clarity:</strong> Measures how much suspended material is left in the water. Clearer water means fewer floating particles and often better conditions for structuring.</li>\n      </ul>\n      <p class="andara-text-lead"><strong>Key idea:</strong> These numbers don’t tell the whole story. But together, they give us a fingerprint of the water’s inner environment — a terrain that can be more or less friendly for coherence, charge and life processes.</p>\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--04 andara-grid--visual">\n        <!-- Visual for How We Measure What Eyes Can’t See -->\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- AI LAYOUT PROMPT: Section on interfaces. Visual: Cross-section illustration of structured water at a surface (e.g., collagen fiber). -->\n  <div class="andara-section">\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <h2>6. Interfaces – Where Water Becomes Biological</h2>\n      <p>Life doesn’t happen in bulk water; it happens where water touches surfaces:</p>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Cell membranes</li>\n        <li>Collagen fibers</li>\n        <li>Gels, fascia, cytoskeleton</li>\n        <li>Rock surfaces, soil particles, ceramic and glass</li>\n      </ul>\n      <p>At these interfaces, water tends to form structured layers:</p>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Partially ordered, EZ-like zones that support charge separation</li>\n        <li>Act as slip layers for blood and lymph</li>\n        <li>Provide proton pathways and ion channels along surfaces</li>\n      </ul>\n      <p>In this view, the body is a liquid crystal: a <a href="/science/crystalline-matrix/overview">crystalline matrix</a> of minerals, proteins and water, continually restructuring itself based on the quality of the water phase.</p>\n      <p class="andara-text-lead"><strong>Key idea:</strong> The question is not only “what’s in your water?” but “what can your water become once it meets the surfaces of life?”</p>\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--01 andara-grid--visual">\n        <!-- Visual for Interfaces – Where Water Becomes Biological -->\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- AI LAYOUT PROMPT: Section on activation in practice. Visual: 4-step horizontal journey from "Tap" to "Activated" water. -->\n  <div class="andara-section">\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <h2>7. From Tap Water to Activated Terrain Water</h2>\n      <p>Most modern water passes through long pipes, pressure, stagnation and chemical treatments. By the time it reaches a glass, it often carries:</p>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Fragmented structures</li>\n        <li>Residual contaminants</li>\n        <li>Disturbed charge distributions</li>\n      </ul>\n      <p>Activation asks a different question:</p>\n      <p class="andara-text-lead">How can we bring water closer to its natural, coherent state before it enters a living system?</p>\n      <p>Typical steps include:</p>\n      <ul>\n        <li><strong>Clarification:</strong> Removing suspended particles, flocculating and filtering out contaminants.</li>\n        <li><strong>Mineral Tuning:</strong> Adjusting the ionic mineral balance (especially sulfates, magnesium, calcium, silicates) to mirror nature’s patterns.</li>\n        <li><strong>Structural Stimulus:</strong> Introducing movement, vortexing, flow paths that re-pattern inner geometry.</li>\n        <li><strong>Energetic Conditioning:</strong> Using light, fields or forms to nudge water into a more coherent, resonant state.</li>\n      </ul>\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--04 andara-grid--visual">\n        <!-- Visual for From Tap Water to Coherent Terrain -->\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- AI LAYOUT PROMPT: Section explaining Andara's role. Visual: simple funnel graphic with Andara's role in the middle. Neutral, technical. -->\n  <div class="andara-section andara-section--brand-context">\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <h2>8. Andara Ionic in the Water Science Context</h2>\n      <p>Andara Ionic is designed as a primordial ionic sulfate mineral solution used to condition and clarify water. Its role sits specifically in the “Mineral Tuning” and “Clarification” stages of the activation journey:</p>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Provides a precisely defined band of ionic sulfates and companion minerals, inspired by natural volcanic–ocean interfaces.</li>\n        <li>Supports flocculation and clarification of water, helping suspended impurities to cluster and fall out.</li>\n        <li>Tunes water towards the 17–30 mg/L sulfate range that often appears in:\n          <ul>\n            <li>Human plasma sulfate levels</li>\n            <li>Classical water treatment optimal windows</li>\n            <li>Interface conditions associated with EZ-like phenomena (in lab contexts)</li>\n          </ul>\n        </li>\n      </ul>\n      <p>From there, the rest of the activation — vortexing, structural devices, light, architecture — can build on a cleaner, better-tuned base.</p>\n      <p class="andara-text-lead"><strong>Key idea:</strong> Andara Ionic is not positioned as a health product here, but as a water-phase tuning instrument — a way of bringing tap or source water closer to the mineral and structural language of natural living waters.</p>\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--01 andara-grid--visual">\n        <!-- Visual for Andara Ionic in the Water Science Context -->\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- AI LAYOUT PROMPT: Summary section. Visual: calm closing image of a clear spring. -->\n  <div class="andara-section andara-section--summary">\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <h2>9. Water Science in One Breath</h2>\n      <p>Water is the moving mirror between matter and consciousness. It shifts phases, reorganizes its structure, stores charge, and responds to every mineral, movement, photon and field it meets.</p>\n      <p>When we talk about phases, structure and activation, we are really talking about:</p>\n      <ul>\n        <li>How water chooses a form (ice, liquid, vapor, structured)</li>\n        <li>How it arranges its molecules (disordered vs coherent)</li>\n        <li>How natural activators — minerals, light, motion, fields — tune it closer to the water of mountain springs and living cells.</li>\n      </ul>\n      <p>This page is an entry point. The deeper layers live in the rest of the <a href="/science/water">Water Science</a> and <a href="/science/minerals">Mineral Science</a> sections of the Andara Library.</p>\n      <p class="andara-cta-soft">Explore next: <a href="/science/water/structured-water">Structured Water</a> – how ordered water forms, how it’s studied, and how it might be recreated at home.</p>\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--01 andara-grid--visual">\n        <!-- Visual for Water Science in One Breath -->\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\nI am ready to create this page in your CMS using the `createPage` function. Please confirm if you want me to proceed with these details.	[{"name": "searchDocuments", "result": []}, {"name": "listPages", "result": [{"id": "d2e1fa08-30e0-4974-a506-9ccb4e50aee4", "path": "/science/water", "title": "Water Science: Understand the Liquid Architecture That Runs Your Life", "status": "published", "cluster": "water_science", "priority": "P2", "template": "cluster_overview"}, {"id": "e52506be-9376-411b-8ceb-f27c803ed588", "path": "/science/water/structured-water", "title": "Structured Water – From Chaos to Coherence", "status": "published", "cluster": "water_science", "priority": "P2", "template": "article"}, {"id": "112a951c-881d-46ff-8299-6e5d64a0782c", "path": "/science/water/ez-water", "title": "EZ Water – Exclusion Zone & Charge Separation", "status": "published", "cluster": "water_science", "priority": "P1", "template": "article"}, {"id": "abb6b523-ec92-48be-8648-91ae8a4a39af", "path": "/science/water/ph-orp-ec", "title": "pH, ORP & EC – Measuring Water's Inner State", "status": "published", "cluster": "water_science", "priority": "P2", "template": "article"}, {"id": "ee99cbbf-adf9-4d28-b5f1-7b942e3d7daa", "path": "/science/water/turbidity", "title": "Turbidity & Clarification – Why Clear Water Matters", "status": "published", "cluster": "water_science", "priority": "P2", "template": "article"}, {"id": "18280890-c648-4cf2-a154-9c770344e67b", "path": "/science/water/hydration-clusters", "title": "Hydration Clusters – How Water Organises Around Charge", "status": "published", "cluster": "water_science", "priority": "P2", "template": "article"}, {"id": "7bd97d86-ec0c-433b-a949-833dc5ce0d3f", "path": "/science/water/water-memory", "title": "Water Memory – Information in the Liquid Matrix", "status": "published", "cluster": "water_science", "priority": "P2", "template": "article"}, {"id": "10532149-0a87-4549-bad5-15a443bad154", "path": "/science/water/vortexing", "title": "Vortexing & Flow Geometry", "status": "published", "cluster": "water_science", "priority": "P2", "template": "article"}, {"id": "724069fe-3c49-476f-82d7-7d737363c38c", "path": "/science/water/magnetics", "title": "Magnetics & Field Effects on Water", "status": "published", "cluster": "water_science", "priority": "P2", "template": "article"}, {"id": "fee3d32f-8c4b-4f87-955a-41bbb48a80d3", "path": "/science/water/natural-springs", "title": "Natural Springs – Earth's Original Water Technology", "status": "published", "cluster": "water_science", "priority": "P2", "tem