<p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Combine the 100&nbsp;ml mineral drops with <strong>vortex devices, magnets,\n            special glassware or flow forms</strong> to explore how sulfate minerals\n            and flow dynamics co-create structured water patterns.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">Plants, gardens &amp; soil tests</h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Use diluted Andara-treated water in <strong>watering cans, sprayers or soil\n            tests</strong> to observe how water clarity, structure and mineral content\n            interact with plant and soil systems – always in a non-medical, ecological context.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">DIY water metrics &amp; lab tracking</h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Use pH, ORP, EC, turbidity and conductivity meters to compare <strong>before vs.\n            after</strong> water parameters when Andara Ionic 100&nbsp;ml is used in the\n            recommended ranges. Document your own data curves over time.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- AI LAYOUT PROMPT – USE SCENARIOS\n  Layout:\n  - Four `.andara-grid__item` cards in `.andara-grid--scenarios`.\n  - Desktop: 2x2 layout, mobile: single column stack.\n  - Each card should feel like a “scenario card” with title + short paragraph.\n\n  Imagery:\n  - For this section, consider 4 small icons or thumbnails:\n    - Jug/carafe with drops.\n    - Swirling vortex device with blue water.\n    - Plant/leaf with a watering can.\n    - Simple lab meters (pH/ORP/EC) next to a glass of water.\n  - Optionally animate subtle hover on each card (slight lift or glow).\n\n  Emotion:\n  - Exploratory, experimental, playful, but still grounded in water science.\n  -->\n\n  <!-- ===========================\n       SECTION 4 – HOW IT WORKS\n  ============================ -->\n  <section\n    id="product-100ml-how-it-works"\n    class="andara-section andara-section--how-it-works"\n    aria-label="How Andara Ionic 100 ml works in water"\n  >\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <header class="andara-section__header">\n        <h2 class="andara-section__headline">\n          How Andara Ionic 100&nbsp;ml works in water\n        </h2>\n        <p class="andara-section__subline">\n          Behind every drop is a <strong>sulfate-based interaction</strong> that\n          supports clarification, flocculation and structured-water formation.\n        </p>\n      </header>\n\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--process">\n        <article class="andara-grid__item andara-grid__item--step">\n          <div class="andara-grid__step-number">1</div>\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">Drop – introduce ionic sulfate minerals</h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            When you add <strong>Andara Ionic drops</strong> to water, you introduce\n            a spectrum of <strong>charged sulfate minerals</strong>. These ions\n            disperse through the water and begin to interact with dissolved\n            substances and suspended particles.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item andara-grid__item--step">\n          <div class="andara-grid__step-number">2</div>\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">Cluster – flocculation &amp; clarification</h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            The charged ions support <strong>coagulation and flocculation</strong>:\n            tiny particles cluster into visible flocs that can settle or be filtered.\n            Over time, many users observe <strong>clearer water and clustered sediments</strong>\n            at the bottom of the container.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item andara-grid__item--step">\n          <div class="andara-grid__step-number">3</div>\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">Structure – sulfate-driven water organization</h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            In the <strong>17–30&nbsp;mg/L sulfate range</strong>, water can adopt\n            more <strong>ordered, liquid-crystalline structures</strong> near mineral\n            and hydrophilic surfaces, similar in behavior to so-called EZ water.\n            This is observed in lab metrics and UV-spectra, not presented as a\n            medical claim.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n      </div>\n\n      <p class="andara-section__note">\n        Andara Ionic 100&nbsp;ml is always described in terms of <strong>water\n        chemistry, structure and physical parameters</strong> – not as a treatment\n        for the human body. All explanations stay within water science and\n        mineral chemistry.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- AI LAYOUT PROMPT – HOW IT WORKS\n  Layout:\n  - Use `.andara-grid--process` as a 3-step horizontal journey.\n  - Desktop: three columns with `.andara-grid__step-number` as a circular or pill-like badge.\n  - Mobile: stack steps 1–3 vertically, numbers still prominent.\n\n  Imagery:\n  - Optionally, a subtle horizontal timeline line behind the three cards.\n  - Each step can use a minimal icon:\n    - Step 1: droplet hitting water surface.\n    - Step 2: particles clustering into a soft sphere.\n    - Step 3: hexagonal/structured water pattern.\n\n  Animation:\n  - Light sequential fade-in or slide-in for steps 1, 2, 3 as user scrolls.\n  -->\n\n  <!-- ===========================\n       SECTION 5 – HOW TO USE / DOSING\n  ============================ -->\n  <section\n    id="product-100ml-how-to-use"\n    class="andara-section andara-section--how-to-use"\n    aria-label="How to use Andara Ionic 100 ml"\n  >\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <header class="andara-section__header">\n        <h2 class="andara-section__headline">\n          How to use Andara Ionic 100&nbsp;ml – simple dosing guidelines\n        </h2>\n        <p class="andara-section__subline">\n          A practical way to reach the <strong>Andara sulfate activation range</strong>\n          in everyday water.\n        </p>\n      </header>\n\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--02">\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">Step-by-step basic use</h3>\n          <ol class="andara-list andara-list--numbered">\n            <li>Fill a clean glass, jug or container with your base water.</li>\n            <li>Add a <strong>measured number of drops or milliliters</strong> of Andara Ionic 100&nbsp;ml according to your preferred dilution.</li>\n            <li>Stir or shake to distribute the minerals evenly.</li>\n            <li>Allow <strong>settling time</strong> so flocs can form and sink.</li>\n            <li>Carefully decant or filter the clarified water, leaving sediments behind.</li>\n          </ol>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">Connection to the activation range</h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            In lab protocols, a dose of around <strong>1&nbsp;ml per liter</strong> is\n            associated with approximately <strong>17–18&nbsp;mg/L sulfate</strong>,\n            which lies inside the Andara activation band of <strong>17–30&nbsp;mg/L</strong>.\n          </p>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            For custom setups, large tanks or special experiments, you can use\n            the <a href="/tools/dilution-calculator">Andara Dilution Calculator</a>\n            to align your volume and desired sulfate range.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n      </div>\n\n      <!-- HIGHLIGHT BOX: SAFETY / POSITIONING -->\n      <div class="andara-callout andara-callout--info">\n        <h3 class="andara-callout__title">Important positi