ails>\n\n      <details class="andara-faq__item">\n        <summary class="andara-faq__question">\n          How long does a 100&nbsp;ml bottle last?\n        </summary>\n        <div class="andara-faq__answer">\n          <p>\n            This depends on how much water you treat and at which dilution.\n            At <strong>small daily use</strong> for personal water jugs, many users\n            find that a bottle can accompany them for weeks. For intensive\n            lab or garden projects, consumption is naturally higher.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </details>\n\n      <details class="andara-faq__item">\n        <summary class="andara-faq__question">\n          Can I use Andara Ionic together with filters and vortex devices?\n        </summary>\n        <div class="andara-faq__answer">\n          <p>\n            Yes. Many users integrate Andara Ionic into a broader water setup:\n            pre-filtration, Andara treatment, settling/filtration again,\n            and then <strong>vortexing or structuring</strong>. The sequence\n            always depends on your system design.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </details>\n\n      <details class="andara-faq__item">\n        <summary class="andara-faq__question">\n          Where can I learn more about the science behind Andara Ionic?\n        </summary>\n        <div class="andara-faq__answer">\n          <p>\n            The <a href="/science">Andara Science Library</a> offers in-depth\n            articles on water science, mineral chemistry, crystalline matrices\n            and bioelectric concepts. Each product page connects into these\n            background pages.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </details>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- AI LAYOUT PROMPT – FAQ\n  Layout:\n  - Standard accordion behavior for each `<details>` element.\n  - Make `.andara-faq__question` bold and easy to scan.\n  - Only one or multiple Q&A can be open at the same time; browser default is fine.\n\n  Imagery:\n  - Minimal – maybe a small question mark icon or calm line-art illustration in the background.\n\n  Emotion:\n  - Reassuring, clear, honest boundaries (no health claims, crystal-clear positioning).\n  -->\n\n  <!-- ===========================\n       SECTION 8 – SCIENCE SNIPPET\n  ============================ -->\n  <section\n    id="product-100ml-science"\n    class="andara-section andara-section--science-snippet"\n    aria-label="Science background for Andara Ionic 100 ml"\n  >\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <header class="andara-section__header">\n        <h2 class="andara-section__headline">\n          Science behind Andara Ionic 100&nbsp;ml\n        </h2>\n        <p class="andara-section__subline">\n          A product page that is directly wired into the <strong>Andara Science Library</strong>.\n        </p>\n      </header>\n\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--02">\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">Water science &amp; structured water</h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Learn how <strong>pH, ORP, EC, turbidity and structured-water phenomena</strong>\n            respond when sulfate minerals are introduced in small, controlled\n            amounts. Explore the connection between Andara and concepts like\n            <strong>EZ water</strong> and <strong>hydration clusters</strong>.\n          </p>\n          <p>\n            <a href="/science/water/overview">Enter Water Science &rarr;</a>\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">Mineral, crystalline &amp; bioelectric view</h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Dive into <strong>ionic vs. colloidal minerals, sulfate chemistry,\n            tetrahedral/hexagonal matrices and cell voltage concepts</strong>.\n            Andara Ionic sits at the intersection of mineral chemistry,\n            crystalline geometry and bioelectric fields.\n          </p>\n          <p>\n            <a href="/science/minerals/overview">Mineral Science &rarr;</a><br />\n            <a href="/science/crystalline/overview">Crystalline Matrix &rarr;</a><br />\n            <a href="/science/bioelectric/overview">Bioelectric Science &rarr;</a>\n          </p>\n        </article>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- AI LAYOUT PROMPT – SCIENCE SNIPPET\n  Layout:\n  - Two columns, each like a “science teaser card”.\n  - Add clear text links that visually look like secondary CTAs.\n\n  Imagery:\n  - Consider a small abstract illustration under each card:\n    - Left: water wave + structural hexagon.\n    - Right: subtle lattice of atoms + light.\n\n  Emotion:\n  - Curious, exploratory, “click and learn more”.\n  -->\n\n  <!-- ===========================\n       SECTION 9 – NEURAL SCIENCE FOOTER\n  ============================ -->\n  <section\n    id="andara-neural-footer"\n    class="andara-section andara-section--footer-science"\n    aria-label="Andara science footer navigation"\n  >\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <header class="andara-section__header">\n        <h2 class="andara-section__headline">\n          Andara Library – start exploring from here\n        </h2>\n        <p class="andara-section__subline">\n          Every product page, including <strong>Andara Ionic 100&nbsp;ml</strong>, connects\n          into a <strong>neural knowledge base</strong> of water, minerals and crystalline science.\n        </p>\n      </header>\n\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--footer-links">\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">Water Science</h3>\n          <ul class="andara-grid__list">\n            <li><a href="/science/water/structured-water">Structured Water</a></li>\n            <li><a href="/science/water/ez-water">EZ Water</a></li>\n            <li><a href="/science/water/ph-orp-ec">pH · ORP · EC</a></li>\n            <li><a href="/science/water/turbidity">Turbidity &amp; clarity</a></li>\n            <li><a href="/science/water/vortexing">Vortexing &amp; flow</a></li>\n          </ul>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">Mineral &amp; Crystalline</h3>\n          <ul class="andara-grid__list">\n            <li><a href="/science/minerals/ionic-vs-colloidal">Ionic vs. colloidal</a></li>\n            <li><a href="/science/minerals/sulfate-chemistry">Sulfate chemistry</a></li>\n            <li><a href="/science/crystalline/tetrahedral-matrix">Tetrahedral matrix</a></li>\n            <li><a href="/science/crystalline/hexagonal-structures">Hexagonal structures</a></li>\n            <li><a href="/science/crystalline/sacred-geometry-bioelectric">Sacred geometry &amp; bioelectricity</a></li>\n          </ul>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">Tools &amp; testing</h3>\n          <ul class="andara-grid__list">\n            <li><a href="/tools/dilution-calculator">Andara Dilution Calculator</a></li>\n            <li><a href="/tools/lab-measurements">Lab measurements (pH · ORP · EC · TDS)</a></li>\n            <li><a href="/guides/structured-water-at-home">Structured water at home</a></li>\n            <li><a href="/blog">Andara Articles</a></li>\n            <li><a href="/contact">Contact &amp; Support</a></li>\n          </ul>\n        </article>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- AI LAYOUT PROMPT – NEURAL FOOTER\n  Layout:\n  - Three columns of link lists inside `.andara-grid--footer-links`.\n  - Desktop: 3 columns; tablet: 2 columns; mobile: 1 column.\n\n  Imagery:\n  - Very minimal; can use soft background lines or nodes hinting at a “neural network” of knowledge.\n\n  Function:\n  - This acts as the “neural science footer engine” – always repeatable on product and science pages\n    for deep internal linking and SEO.\n  -->\n</div>	\N
112a951c-881d-46ff-8299-6e5d64a0782c	water_ez	EZ Water – Exclusion Zone & Charge Separation	/science/water/ez-water	article	article	water_science	science_water_overview	3	\N	\N	ez water and structured water	\N	\N	\N	\N	published	{}	\N	2025-12-08 03:00:05.492531	2025-12-09 18:16:30.526	\N	\N	\N	[]	[]	{"pageId": "water_ez", "cluster": "water_science", "priority": "P1", "vibeKeywords": ["fourth phase", "liquid crystal water", "interfacial layers", "hexagonal sheets", "soft plasma-like", "deep indigo", "aqua-turquoise", "soft gold nodes"], "aiImagePrompt": "A hydrophilic surface on the left, with a glowing, semi-transparent band of hexagonal water layers extending out into deep indigo space. Within this band, ions and electrons flow as tiny sparks, while small particles are excluded beyond the boundary. Mood: precise, mystical, liquid crystal, calm.", "aiVideoPrompt": "A subtle, looping background video showing faint honeycomb patterns and hexagonal layers slowly sliding over each other. A glowing, semi-transparent EZ band gently expands and contracts, with tiny sparks of light (ions) moving within it. The overall mood is calm, precise, and scientific yet mystical.", "designerNotes": "The Fourth Phase of Water page should feel like zooming into the interface where life happens: a thin, glowing band of structured water between solid and liquid. Visual language: hexagons, soft gradients, charge separation, microspheres excluded from a luminous layer. Keep everything terrain-focused and non-medical.", "emotionalTone": ["revelation", "wonder", "inner-recognition", "calm precision", "future-organic", "sacred-scientific"], "animationIdeas": ["hexagonal layers slowly sliding over each other", "a surface with a glowing EZ band extending from it", "microspheres being gently pushed out of a charged zone", "hover: cards show small hexagon grids fading in", "timeline: EZ region expanding with IR-light pulses", "background: faint honeycomb patterns moving slowly"]}	import React from "react"\nimport { motion, MotionConfig } from "motion/react"\n\n/*\nANDARA VISUAL CONFIG:\npageId: "water-fourth-phase"\ncluster: "Science Library · Water"\npriority: "P1"\nvibeKeywords: [\n  "fourth phase",\n  "liquid crystal water",\n  "interfacial layers",\n  "hexagonal sheets",\n  "soft plasma-like",\n  "deep indigo",\n  "aqua-turquoise",\n  "soft gold nodes"\n]\nemotionalTone: [\n  "revelation",\n  "wonder",\n  "inner-recognition",\n  "calm precision",\n  "future-organic",\n  "sacred-scientific"\n]\nanimationIdeas: [\n  "hexagonal layers slowly sliding over each other",\n  "a surface with a glowing EZ band extending from it",\n  "microspheres being gently pushed out of a charged zone",\n  "hover: cards show small hexagon grids fading in",\n  "timeline: EZ region expanding with IR-light pulses",\n  "background: faint honeycomb patterns moving slowly"\n]\naiImagePromptHero: "A hydrophilic surface on the left, with a glowing, semi-transparent band of hexagonal water layers extending out into deep indigo space. Within this band, ions and electrons flow as tiny sparks, while small particles are excluded beyond the boundary. Mood: precise, mystical, liquid crystal, calm."\ndesignerNotes: "The Fourth Phase of Water page should feel like zooming into the interface where life happens: a thin, glowing band of structured water between solid and liquid. Visual language: hexagons, soft gradients, charge separation, microspheres excluded from a luminous layer. Keep everything terrain-focused and non-medical."\n*/\n\n// shared animation tokens (same as other Andara science pages)\nconst fadeUp: Record<string, any> = {\n  hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 24 },\n  visible: { opacity: 1, y: 0 },\n}\n\nconst fadeUpContainer: Record<string, any> = {\n  hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 16 },\n  visible: {\n    opacity: 1,\n    y: 0,\n    transition: {\n      staggerChildren: 0.06,\n    },\n  },\n}\n\nconst fadeChild: Record<string, any> = {\n  hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 16 },\n  visible: { opacity: 1, y: 0 },\n}\n\nexport const FourthPhaseOfWaterPage: React.FC = () => {\n  return (\n    <MotionConfig transition={{ duration: 0.7, ease: "easeOut" }}>\n      <main\n        id="andara-fourth-phase"\n        className="andara-page andara-page--science"\n        aria-label="The Fourth Phase of Water – Liquid Crystal Behaviour in Terrain"\n      >\n        {/* =========================\n             HERO – FOURTH PHASE\n        ========================== */}\n        <motion.section\n          id="fourth-phase-hero"\n          className="andara-hero andara-hero--primary"\n          aria-label="Fourth Phase of Water main introduction"\n          initial="hidden"\n          animate="visible"\n          variants={fadeUpContainer}\n        >\n          <div className="andara-hero__inner">\n            <header className="andara-hero__content">\n              <motion.p\n                className="andara-hero__label"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                Science Library · Water · Fourth Phase (EZ-Water)\n              </motion.p>\n\n              <motion.h1\n                className="andara-hero__headline"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                The Fourth Phase of Water: The Hidden Liquid Crystal State that Powers Terrain\n              </motion.h1>\n\n              <motion.p\n                className="andara-hero__subline"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <span className="andara-text-lead">\n                  Beyond solid, liquid, and vapor, water can enter a <strong>fourth phase</strong>:\n                  a structured, liquid crystal state that forms next to <strong>surfaces</strong>.\n                </span>{" "}\n                In this state, water behaves like a <strong>soft crystal</strong> – storing charge,\n                excluding particles, and becoming a <strong>tiny battery</strong> at the interface\n                where life is built.\n              </motion.p>\n\n              <motion.ul\n                className="andara-hero__bullets"\n                variants={fadeUpContainer}\n              >\n                <motion.li variants={fadeChild}>\n                  <strong>Interfacial structuring:</strong> how water forms ordered layers next to\n                  hydrophilic surfaces.\n                </motion.li>\n                <motion.li variants={fadeChild}>\n                  <strong>Charge separation:</strong> why EZ-water tends to be <strong>negatively charged</strong> and\n                  pushes protons away.\n                </motion.li>\n                <motion.li variants={fadeChild}>\n                  <strong>Terrain relevance:</strong> what this means for <strong>fascia, gels, capillaries,\n                  and cellular interfaces</strong>.\n                </motion.li>\n              </motion.ul>\n            </header>\n\n            <motion.figure\n              className="andara-hero__media"\n              variants={fadeChild}\n            >\n              <motion.div\n                className="andara-hero__media-placeholder"\n                initial={{ opacity: 0, scale: 0.96 }}\n                animate={{ opacity: 1, scale: [1, 1.02, 1] }}\n                transition={{\n                  duration: 1.6,\n                  repeat: Infinity,\n                  repeatType: "mirror",\n                }}\n              >\n                <p>\n                  [Hero visual: a hydrophilic surface on the left, with a glowing, semi-transparent band of hexagonal\n                  water layers extending out. Tiny charged particles move within the band, while small spheres are held\n                  outside. Background fades into deep indigo with aqua-turquoise caustic patterns.]\n                </p>\n              </motion.div>\n              <motion.figcaption\n                className="andara-hero__media-caption"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                The fourth phase of water is a structured, interfacial state – a thin, liquid crystal band that behaves\n                like a tiny battery everywhere water meets surfaces.\n              </motion.figcaption>\n            </motion.figure>\n          </div>\n        </motion.section>\n\n        {/* =========================\n             SECTION – WHAT IS THE FOURTH PHASE?\n        ========================== */}\n        <motion.section\n          id="fourth-phase-what-is-it"\n          className="andara-section andara-section--what-it-is"\n          aria-label="What is the fourth phase of water"\n          initial="hidden"\n          whileInView="visible"\n          viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-20%" }}\n          variants={fadeUp}\n        >\n          <div className="andara-section__inner">\n            <header className="andara-section__header">\n              <h2 className="andara-section__headline">\n                What Do We Mean by “The Fourth Phase of Water”?\n              </h2>\n              <p className="andara-section__subline">\n                <span className="andara-text-lead">\n                  The fourth phase of water is often called <strong>EZ-water</strong> (Exclusion Zone water).\n                </span>{" "}\n                It forms at the boundary where water meets certain <strong>hydrophilic surfaces</strong> – like gels,\n                proteins, and membranes – and behaves differently from ordinary bulk water.\n              </p>\n            </header>\n\n            <motion.div\n              className="andara-grid andara-grid--03 andara-section__items"\n              variants={fadeUpContainer}\n            >\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">\n                  1. A Liquid Crystal Layer\n                </h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  In the fourth phase, water molecules arrange into more <strong>ordered, sheet-like structures</strong>.\n                  It is still water – not ice – but behaves more like a <strong>soft crystal</strong>, with distinct\n                  physical properties.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">\n                  2. Exclusion of Particles\n                </h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  These interfacial layers tend to <strong>exclude solutes and microspheres</strong>. Small particles\n                  are pushed out, leaving a region of comparatively <strong>pure, ordered water</strong> next to the\n                  surface – hence the name “Exclusion Zone”.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">\n                  3. Natural Charge Separation\n                </h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  EZ-water often carries a <strong>net negative charge</strong>, while positively charged protons are\n                  pushed into the surrounding bulk. This creates a tiny <strong>battery-like separation</strong> of\n                  charge right at the interface.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n            </motion.div>\n\n            <motion.figure\n              className="andara-figure andara-figure--ez-overview"\n              variants={fadeChild}\n            >\n              <div className="andara-figure__visual">\n                <p>\n                  [Infographic: a surface at left, labelled “Hydrophilic Surface”; a band next to it labelled\n                  “Fourth Phase / EZ (–)”; further out, “Bulk Water (+)” with small particles floating.\n                  Arrows show protons moving away, electrons staying in the EZ.]\n                </p>\n              </div>\n              <figcaption className="andara-figure__caption">\n                The fourth phase of water emerges right at hydrophilic surfaces – forming a negatively charged,\n                particle-excluding zone that behaves like a liquid crystal.\n              </figcaption>\n            </motion.figure>\n          </div>\n        </motion.section>\n\n        {/* =========================\n             SECTION – KEY PROPERTIES OF THE FOURTH PHASE\n        ========================== */}\n        <motion.section\n          id="fourth-phase-properties"\n          className="andara-section andara-section--properties"\n          aria-label="Properties of the fourth phase of water"\n          initial="hidden"\n          whileInView="visible"\n          viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-20%" }}\n          variants={fadeUp}\n        >\n          <div className="andara-section__inner">\n            <header className="andara-section__header">\n              <h2 className="andara-section__headline">\n                Key Properties: What Makes the Fourth Phase Different?\n              </h2>\n              <p className="andara-section__subline">\n                <span className="andara-text-lead">\n                  Experiments suggest that the fourth phase of water has <strong>distinct physical and electrical behaviours</strong>.\n                </span>{" "}\n                These properties matter when we think about water at <strong>biological interfaces</strong>, not just in a glass.\n              </p>\n            </header>\n\n            <motion.div\n              className="andara-grid andara-grid--04 andara-section__items"\n              variants={fadeUpContainer}\n            >\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">1. Exclusion of Solutes</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  Microspheres and certain solutes are <strong>pushed out</strong> of the EZ region, accumulating at\n                  its boundary. This creates a clearer, more ordered band of water close to the surface.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">2. Negative Charge Dominance</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  EZ-water tends to carry more <strong>electrons</strong>, making it relatively negatively charged.\n                  Protons are displaced into the bulk, setting up a <strong>natural voltage difference</strong>.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">3. Increased Viscosity &amp; Structure</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  Compared to bulk water, EZ-water behaves as if it is slightly more <strong>viscous and structured</strong>,\n                  consistent with a <strong>liquid crystal</strong>-like state rather than a random liquid.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">4. Light-Responsive Expansion</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  Experiments indicate that <strong>infrared and visible light</strong> can cause EZ regions to\n                  <strong> expand</strong>. Light, in this view, is not just illumination – it’s an <strong>energy source</strong>\n                  for structured water layers.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n            </motion.div>\n\n            <motion.figure\n              className="andara-figure andara-figure--properties"\n              variants={fadeChild}\n            >\n              <div className="andara-figure__visual">\n                <p>\n                  [Diagram: four small panels labelled “Exclusion”, “Charge Separation”, “Liquid Crystal”, “Light Driven\n                  Expansion”, each with a simple icon: sphere cluster pushed out, plus/minus separation, hexagon grid,\n                  IR wave arrow.]\n                </p>\n              </div>\n              <figcaption className="andara-figure__caption">\n                The fourth phase behaves like a semi-ordered, charge-rich, light-responsive layer – a tiny, self-assembling\n                interface technology built into water itself.\n              </figcaption>\n            </motion.figure>\n          </div>\n        </motion.section>\n\n        {/* =========================\n             SECTION – SIMPLE LAB OBSERVATIONS (NON-PROPRIETARY SUMMARY)\n        ========================== */}\n        <motion.section\n          id="fourth-phase-experiments"\n          className="andara-section andara-section--experiments"\n          aria-label="Fourth phase simple experimental observations"\n          initial="hidden"\n          whileInView="visible"\n          viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-20%" }}\n          variants={fadeUp}\n        >\n          <div className="andara-section__inner">\n            <header className="andara-section__header">\n              <h2 className="andara-section__headline">\n                How Do We Know It Exists? Simple Lab Observations\n              </h2>\n              <p className="andara-section__subline">\n                <span className="andara-text-lead">\n                  A number of experiments – many popularised by researchers like Gerald Pollack – indicate that\n                  <strong> interfacial water behaves differently</strong> from bulk water.\n                </span>{" "}\n                Here is a simplified, non-technical summary.\n              </p>\n            </header>\n\n            <motion.div\n              className="andara-grid andara-grid--03 andara-section__items"\n              variants={fadeUpContainer}\n            >\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Microsphere Exclusion</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  When tiny beads are suspended in water next to certain surfaces, they tend to\n                  <strong> move away from the interface</strong>. A clear zone appears, free of beads, whose size\n                  can change with conditions like <strong>light</strong>.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Voltage &amp; Current Measurements</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  Electrodes placed in the EZ and bulk regions can detect a <strong>voltage difference</strong>.\n                  In some configurations, this charge separation can drive small <strong>electrical currents</strong>,\n                  acting like a basic battery.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Flow &amp; Self-Organisation</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  Droplets and microspheres can show <strong>directed motion</strong> along gradients of\n                  structure and charge. This suggests that interfacial water may help <strong>organise flows</strong>\n                  in ways that are not obvious from bulk behaviour.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n            </motion.div>\n\n            <motion.figure\n              className="andara-figure andara-figure--lab"\n              variants={fadeChild}\n            >\n              <div className="andara-figure__visual">\n                <p>\n                  [Storyboard: 3 small panels – (1) beaker with beads and a clear EZ band; (2) electrodes showing a small\n                  voltage reading; (3) arrow indicating bead motion along a structured interface.]\n                </p>\n              </div>\n              <figcaption className="andara-figure__caption">\n                These lab observations don’t “prove everything”, but they strongly suggest that\n                <strong> next-to-surface water</strong> enters a distinct, structured phase with its own rules.\n              </figcaption>\n            </motion.figure>\n          </div>\n        </motion.section>\n\n        {/* =========================\n             SECTION – WHERE DOES THE FOURTH PHASE SHOW UP IN TERRAIN?\n        ========================== */}\n        <motion.section\n          id="fourth-phase-terrain"\n          className="andara-section andara-section--terrain"\n          aria-label="Fourth phase of water in terrain"\n          initial="hidden"\n          whileInView="visible"\n          viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-20%" }}\n          variants={fadeUp}\n        >\n          <div className="andara-section__inner">\n            <header className="andara-section__header">\n              <h2 className="andara-section__headline">\n                Where Might the Fourth Phase Show Up in a Living Terrain?\n              </h2>\n              <p className="andara-section__subline">\n                <span className="andara-text-lead">\n                  The most interesting part of the fourth phase story is not the lab glassware – it’s the\n                  <strong> interfaces inside living systems</strong>.\n                </span>{" "}\n                Wherever water meets a hydrophilic surface, a fourth phase region may be forming and dissolving\n                continuously.\n              </p>\n            </header>\n\n            <motion.div\n              className="andara-grid andara-grid--04 andara-section__items"\n              variants={fadeUpContainer}\n            >\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Fascia &amp; Connective Tissue</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  The hydrated collagen and ground substance of fascia provide <strong>large hydrophilic surfaces</strong>.\n                  Here, fourth phase water could support <strong>charge storage, glide, and signal transmission</strong>.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Capillaries &amp; Microcirculation</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  In very small vessels and channels, structured water layers may influence\n                  <strong> flow resistance, charge, and separation of components</strong>.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Cell Membranes &amp; Organelles</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  At the scale of <strong>cell membranes, mitochondrial linings, and protein surfaces</strong>,\n                  interfacial water might mediate how <strong>charges move and reactions proceed</strong>.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Soil Gels &amp; Microbial Films</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  In soil and biofilms, fourth phase behaviour may help organise <strong>nutrient flows,\n                  microbial communication, and charge separation</strong> in the rhizosphere.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n            </motion.div>\n\n            <motion.figure\n              className="andara-figure andara-figure--body-map"\n              variants={fadeChild}\n            >\n              <div className="andara-figure__visual">\n                <p>\n                  [Visual: simplified outline of a body and a plant root, with highlighted interface zones\n                  (fascia sheets, capillaries, cell membrane, root/soil boundary) all labelled “Potential EZ Regions”.]\n                </p>\n              </div>\n              <figcaption className="andara-figure__caption">\n                Wherever water meets hydrophilic structure, a fourth phase may flicker in and out – quietly shaping the\n                way terrain stores charge and organises flow.\n              </figcaption>\n            </motion.figure>\n          </div>\n        </motion.section>\n\n        {/* =========================\n             SECTION – FOURTH PHASE VS THE THREE FAMILIAR PHASES\n        ========================== */}\n        <motion.section\n          id="fourth-phase-compare"\n          className="andara-section andara-section--compare"\n          aria-label="Fourth phase vs other phases of water"\n          initial="hidden"\n          whileInView="visible"\n          viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-20%" }}\n          variants={fadeUp}\n        >\n          <div className="andara-section__inner">\n            <header className="andara-section__header">\n              <h2 className="andara-section__headline">\n                How Is the Fourth Phase Different from Solid, Liquid, and Vapor?\n              </h2>\n              <p className="andara-section__subline">\n                <span className="andara-text-lead">\n                  Classical physics textbooks list three states for water: solid, liquid, gas.\n                </span>{" "}\n                The fourth phase doesn’t replace them – it\n                <strong> adds an interfacial state</strong> that only appears under certain conditions.\n              </p>\n            </header>\n\n            <motion.div\n              className="andara-grid andara-grid--04 andara-section__items"\n              variants={fadeUpContainer}\n            >\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item andara-grid__item--compact"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Solid (Ice)</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  Fixed lattice, low mobility, strong structure. Temperature-dependent, bulk property.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item andara-grid__item--compact"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Liquid</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  Mobile, disordered network. Everyday drinking water, bulk behaviour, high mobility.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item andara-grid__item--compact"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Vapor</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  Molecules far apart, gas behaviour, diffusion-dominated, low density.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item andara-grid__item--compact"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Fourth Phase / EZ</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  Semi-ordered, liquid crystal-like, <strong>interfacial</strong> state; occurs near surfaces,\n                  with charge separation and exclusion behaviour.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n            </motion.div>\n\n            <motion.figure\n              className="andara-figure andara-figure--compare"\n              variants={fadeChild}\n            >\n              <div className="andara-figure__visual">\n                <p>\n                  [Diagram: four columns for Ice, Liquid, Vapor, Fourth Phase, with simple icons and 2–3 bullet\n                  keywords under each. Fourth phase column highlighted with a glow.]\n                </p>\n              </div>\n              <figcaption className="andara-figure__caption">\n                The fourth phase doesn’t change the textbook phases – it adds an interfacial, liquid crystal behaviour\n                that is especially relevant to <strong>living terrains</strong>.\n              </figcaption>\n            </motion.figure>\n          </div>\n        </motion.section>\n\n        {/* =========================\n             SECTION – FOURTH PHASE, LIGHT & MINERALS (ANDARA VIEW)\n        ========================== */}\n        <motion.section\n          id="fourth-phase-andara-link"\n          className="andara-section andara-section--product-link"\n          aria-label="Linking fourth phase, light and minerals in the Andara perspective"\n          initial="hidden"\n          whileInView="visible"\n          viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-20%" }}\n          variants={fadeUp}\n        >\n          <div className="andara-section__inner">\n            <header className="andara-section__header">\n              <h2 className="andara-section__headline">\n                Light, Minerals, and the Fourth Phase – The Andara Perspective\n              </h2>\n              <p className="andara-section__subline">\n                <span className="andara-text-lead">\n                  In the Andara universe, the fourth phase is a bridge concept:\n                </span>{" "}\n                it links <strong>light, minerals, and structure</strong> into one picture of how water\n                <strong> can behave at interfaces</strong>.\n              </p>\n            </header>\n\n            <motion.div\n              className="andara-grid andara-grid--03 andara-section__items"\n              variants={fadeUpContainer}\n            >\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Light as a Fourth Phase Catalyst</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  Infrared and visible light can <strong>expand EZ regions</strong>. In terrain language, this hints at\n                  why <strong>sunlight, warmth, and natural IR sources</strong> could matter for water behaviour at\n                  surfaces – in both body and soil contexts.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Minerals as Structural Allies</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  Charged species – especially <strong>ionic minerals</strong> – can influence how water\n                  <strong>organises near surfaces</strong>. Sulfate, magnesium, and trace elements may help shape\n                  <strong> interface geometry and charge buffering</strong>.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Andara Ionic’s Role (Non-Medical)</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  Andara Ionic is presented not as a “treatment”, but as a\n                  <strong> volcanic ionic sulfate mineral code</strong> that can be added in micro-doses to\n                  filtered water – tending to <strong>mineral context and potential structuring behaviour</strong>\n                  of the medium itself.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n            </motion.div>\n\n            <motion.div\n              className="andara-highlight-box andara-highlight-box--cta"\n              variants={fadeChild}\n            >\n              <p className="andara-highlight-box__text">\n                Product details – dilution examples, sulfate ranges, and logistics – live on the{" "}\n                <a href="/shop/andara-ionic-100ml">Andara Ionic 100&nbsp;ml</a> and{" "}\n                <a href="/shop/andara-ionic-1l">1&nbsp;L</a> pages. This Fourth Phase page stays focused on\n                <strong> understanding interfacial water behaviour</strong> from a terrain-first, non-medical viewpoint.\n              </p>\n            </motion.div>\n          </div>\n        </motion.section>\n\n        {/* =========================\n             SECTION – SIMPLE STORYBOARD: EZ-DEPLETED VS EZ-SUPPORTED\n        ========================== */}\n        <motion.section\n          id="fourth-phase-storyboard"\n          className="andara-section andara-section--timeline"\n          aria-label="Fourth phase storyboard – from depleted to supported"\n          initial="hidden"\n          whileInView="visible"\n          viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-20%" }}\n          variants={fadeUp}\n        >\n          <div className="andara-section__inner">\n            <header className="andara-section__header">\n              <h2 className="andara-section__headline">\n                A Simple Storyboard: From EZ-Depleted to EZ-Supported Terrain\n              </h2>\n              <p className="andara-section__subline">\n                <span className="andara-text-lead">\n                  This is not a diagnosis or a protocol – just a <strong>visual metaphor</strong>\n                  for how a terrain might feel when its fourth phase behaviour is <strong>underfed vs supported</strong>.\n                </span>\n              </p>\n            </header>\n\n            <motion.div\n              className="andara-grid andara-grid--timeline andara-section__items"\n              variants={fadeUpContainer}\n            >\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item andara-grid__item--step"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <div className="andara-grid__step-number">1</div>\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Thin, Fragmented EZ Layers</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  Water is <strong>chemically burdened</strong>, interfaces are under-lit and mineral-poor,\n                  and fourth phase regions remain <strong>small and unstable</strong>.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item andara-grid__item--step"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <div className="andara-grid__step-number">2</div>\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Clearing &amp; Basic Ordering</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  Filtration, basic mineral balance, and natural light exposure begin to offer\n                  <strong> clearer interfaces</strong>, making it easier for EZ regions to form.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item andara-grid__item--step"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <div className="andara-grid__step-number">3</div>\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Expanded, More Stable EZ Layers</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  Structured water behaviour, micro-mineral codes, and gentle flow support\n                  <strong> larger, more coherent fourth phase regions</strong> at key interfaces.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item andara-grid__item--step"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <div className="andara-grid__step-number">4</div>\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Terrain as a Coherent Interface Network</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  The terrain behaves more like a <strong>connected matrix</strong> of interfaces instead of isolated\n                  compartments – a network of <strong>charged, structured surfaces</strong> that can store and share\n                  information.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n            </motion.div>\n\n            <motion.figure\n              className="andara-figure andara-figure--timeline"\n              variants={fadeChild}\n            >\n              <div className="andara-figure__visual">\n                <p>\n                  [Timeline visual: from left to right, surfaces with almost no EZ glow,\n                  then a faint band, then a thicker band with hexagonal patterns, then a network of glowing interfaces\n                  throughout a simplified body/terrain sketch.]\n                </p>\n              </div>\n              <figcaption className="andara-figure__caption">\n                The fourth phase can be imagined as an interface network – thin or thick, fragmented or coherent –\n                depending on how water, light, and minerals are invited to work together.\n              </figcaption>\n            </motion.figure>\n          </div>\n        </motion.section>\n\n        {/* =========================\n             SECTION – FAQ (FOURTH PHASE CLARIFICATIONS)\n        ========================== */}\n        <motion.section\n          id="fourth-phase-faq"\n          className="andara-section andara-section--faq"\n          aria-label="Fourth phase of water frequently asked questions"\n          initial="hidden"\n          whileInView="visible"\n          viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-20%" }}\n          variants={fadeUp}\n        >\n          <div className="andara-section__inner">\n            <header className="andara-section__header">\n              <h2 className="andara-section__headline">\n                Fourth Phase of Water – Gentle Clarifications\n              </h2>\n              <p className="andara-section__subline">\n                A few common questions, answered from a <strong>field-first, non-medical</strong> perspective.\n              </p>\n            </header>\n\n            <motion.div\n              className="andara-faq"\n              variants={fadeUpContainer}\n            >\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-faq__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-faq__question">\n                  Is the fourth phase of water universally accepted science?\n                </h3>\n                <p className="andara-faq__answer">\n                  The idea of a distinct, structured interfacial phase has strong experimental support, but\n                 {" "}\n                  <strong>discussion and debate</strong> continue in scientific communities.\n                  {" "}\n                  This page presents the concept as a <strong>useful lens</strong> for thinking about water and\n                  interfaces, not as a final verdict.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-faq__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-faq__question">\n                  Does fourth phase water mean I should buy specific “EZ” products?\n                </h3>\n                <p className="andara-faq__answer">\n                  The concept itself is <strong>not owned by any brand or device</strong>.\n                  {" "}\n                  It emerges wherever water, surfaces, light, and minerals interact in certain ways.\n                  {" "}\n                  Products can attempt to work with these principles, but the underlying behaviour is part of\n                  <strong> nature’s own toolkit</strong>.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-faq__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-faq__question">\n                  Is this page giving medical advice or treatment claims?\n                </h3>\n                <p className="andara-faq__answer">\n                  No.\n                  {" "}\n                  Everything here is <strong>educational</strong> and explores how water might behave at interfaces.\n                  {" "}\n                  It does not diagnose, treat, or replace medical care.\n                  {" "}\n                  The goal is to offer a <strong>terrain-first way</strong> of imagining water’s role in living systems.\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n            </motion.div>\n          </div>\n        </motion.section>\n\n        {/* =========================\n             SECTION – SCIENCE LIBRARY FOOTER\n        ========================== */}\n        <motion.section\n          id="fourth-phase-science-footer"\n          className="andara-section andara-section--library-footer"\n          aria-label="Science Library navigation footer"\n          initial="hidden"\n          whileInView="visible"\n          viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-20%" }}\n          variants={fadeUp}\n        >\n          <div className="andara-section__inner">\n            <header className="andara-section__header">\n              <h2 className="andara-section__headline">\n                Continue Exploring the Andara Science Library\n              </h2>\n              <p className="andara-section__subline">\n                <span className="andara-text-lead">\n                  The fourth phase of water is one piece of a larger architecture.\n                </span>{" "}\n                Water, minerals, bioelectricity, and crystalline geometry\n                <strong> interlock like a living circuit</strong>.\n              </p>\n            </header>\n\n            <motion.div\n              className="andara-grid andara-grid--04 andara-grid--library-footer andara-section__items"\n              aria-label="Science Library pillars"\n              variants={fadeUpContainer}\n            >\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Water Science</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  The broader liquid architecture – pH, ORP, EC, and structured water behaviour.\n                </p>\n                <p className="andara-grid__link">\n                  <a href="/science/water">Go to Water Science →</a>\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Bioelectricity</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  Voltage gradients, charge, and fields – the electrical side of the terrain.\n                </p>\n                <p className="andara-grid__link">\n                  <a href="/science/bioelectricity">Go to Bioelectricity →</a>\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Mineral Science</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  How different mineral forms and ions speak to water and tissues.\n                </p>\n                <p className="andara-grid__link">\n                  <a href="/science/minerals">Go to Mineral Science →</a>\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n\n              <motion.article\n                className="andara-grid__item"\n                variants={fadeChild}\n              >\n                <h3 className="andara-grid__title">Crystalline Matrix</h3>\n                <p className="andara-grid__text">\n                  Geometry, lattices, and the mineral-light matrix behind coherence.\n                </p>\n                <p className="andara-grid__link">\n                  <a href="/science/crystalline-matrix">Go to Crystalline Matrix →</a>\n                </p>\n              </motion.article>\n            </motion.div>\n\n            <motion.div\n              className="andara-highlight-box andara-highlight-box--neural-footer"\n              variants={fadeChild}\n            >\n              <p className="andara-highlight-box__text">\n                The <strong>Andara Library Engine</strong> is designed as a <strong>semantic circuit</strong> – whichever\n                pillar you enter through, you can always trace the connections back to the whole.\n              </p>\n            </motion.div>\n          </div>\n        </motion.section>\n\n        {/* =========================\n             FINAL CTA\n        ========================== */}\n        <motion.section\n          id="fourth-phase-final-cta"\n          className="andara-section andara-section--final-cta"\n          aria-label="Final call to action"\n          initial="hidden"\n          whileInView="visible"\n          viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-20%" }}\n          variants={fadeUp}\n        >\n          <div className="andara-section__inner">\n            <div className="andara-final-cta__content">\n              <h2 className="andara-final-cta__headline">\n                When you honour the interfaces, you honour the intelligence of water.\n              </h2>\n              <p className="andara-final-cta__text">\n                If the fourth phase of water <strong>resonates</strong> with you, you don’t need to chase exotic ideas.\n                {" "}\n                Begin with what you can touch:\n                {" "}\n                <strong>the water you drink, the light you invite, and the mineral stories you add</strong>.\n                {" "}\n                The terrain continually reshapes its fourth phase architecture in response to these quiet choices.\n              </p>\n              <div className="andara-final-cta__cta-group">\n                <a\n                  href="/shop"\n                  className="andara-final-cta__cta andara-final-cta__cta--primary"\n                >\n                  Explore Andara Ionic Formats\n                </a>\n                <a\n                  href="/science"\n                  className="andara-final-cta__cta a