       Andara Ionic works in the same <strong>sulfate concentration band</strong> seen in\n          <strong>biology, classical water treatment, and lab studies</strong> – turning ordinary water into a\n          <strong>clearer, more coherent medium</strong>, without saturating it with salt or heavy additives.\n        </p>\n        <ul class="andara-hero__bullets">\n          <li>\n            <strong>Volcanic origin:</strong> derived from deep-crust mica and allied minerals with a rich elemental fingerprint.\n          </li>\n          <li>\n            <strong>Fully ionic &amp; sulfated:</strong> all key elements dissolved as <strong>sulfate complexes</strong>, ready to interact with water.\n          </li>\n          <li>\n            <strong>Micro-dose, macro-effect:</strong> typical use in the <strong>17–30&nbsp;mg/L sulfate band</strong>\n            – small amounts, big shift in clarity and charge behaviour.\n          </li>\n        </ul>\n        <div class="andara-hero__cta-group">\n          <a\n            href="#andara-ionic-activation"\n            class="andara-hero__cta andara-hero__cta--primary"\n          >\n            See how it works in water\n          </a>\n        </div>\n        <p class="andara-hero__support-text">\n          Or go directly to the\n          <a href="/andara-dilution-calculator" class="andara-hero__support-link">\n            Andara Dilution Calculator\n          </a>\n          and\n          <a href="/shop" class="andara-hero__support-link">\n            product formats\n          </a>.\n        </p>\n      </header>\n\n      <figure class="andara-hero__media">\n        <div class="andara-hero__media-placeholder">\n          <p>\n            [Hero visual: a dark blue Andara Ionic bottle labelled\n            “Primordial Ionic Sulfate Minerals” next to a glass of water.\n            Behind them: a stylized volcano, glowing mineral crystals, and subtle hexagonal light patterns inside the water.]\n          </p>\n        </div>\n        <figcaption class="andara-hero__media-caption">\n          From volcano to glass – a sulfated ionic mineral complex designed to work with water itself.\n        </figcaption>\n      </figure>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!--\n  REPLIT / MOTION LAYOUT PROMPT – HERO\n  - Layout:\n    - Two-column hero: left text (~60%), right product visual (~40%).\n    - Desktop: text left, image right; mobile: stack with text first.\n  - Imagery:\n    - Show actual Andara-style bottle shape if known (dark glass, minimal label).\n    - Place clear “before/after” glasses subtly in background: one slightly turbid, one clear and glowing.\n  - Motion (Framer Motion dictionary):\n    - Background: `ambient-water-ripple` + `ambient-volcanic-glow` under the hero.\n    - Headline + bullets: `scroll-fade-up-stagger`.\n    - Bottle + water glass: `crystalline-shimmer-slow` loop, very subtle.\n  - Vibe:\n    - Precision, trust, origin. It should feel like a bridge between a Japanese-style volcanic spring and a clean research lab.\n  -->\n\n  <!-- =========================\n       SECTION – WHAT IT IS\n  ========================== -->\n  <section\n    id="andara-ionic-what-it-is"\n    class="andara-section andara-section--what-it-is"\n    aria-label="What Andara Ionic is"\n  >\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <header class="andara-section__header">\n        <h2 class="andara-section__headline">\n          What Andara Ionic Actually Is – Beyond “Just Minerals”\n        </h2>\n        <p class="andara-section__subline">\n          <span class="andara-text-lead">\n            Andara Ionic is not a salt, not a fulvic concentrate, and not a simple plant extract.\n          </span>\n          It is a <strong>volcanic sulfate-based ionic mineral complex</strong> crafted from\n          deep-crust mineral sources, where each element is brought into a <strong>fully dissolved, sulfated state</strong>\n          so it can interact directly with water’s charge and structure.\n        </p>\n      </header>\n\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--03 andara-section__items">\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            1. Volcanic Origin\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            The story starts in <strong>volcanic strata</strong>, with minerals such as\n            <strong>biotite/mica and allied rocks</strong> that carry iron, magnesium, calcium, aluminum,\n            silica and rare-earth elements. These deep-crust matrices encode a <strong>rich elemental fingerprint</strong>\n            that is very different from standard sea salt.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            2. Ionic Sulfate Transformation\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Through a controlled process, these solids are transformed into <strong>ionic sulfates</strong> –\n            all key minerals dissolve into <strong>clear liquid form</strong>. This is not a suspension or colloid:\n            the elements are present as <strong>charged ionic pairs</strong>, especially sulfate complexes (SO₄²⁻),\n            ready to drive <strong>flocculation and charge re-ordering</strong> in water.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            3. Primordial Concentrate for Micro-Dosing\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            The result is a <strong>primordial concentrate</strong> used at very small doses, typically around\n            <strong>1&nbsp;ml per liter</strong> of water, bringing the sulfate content into the\n            <strong>17–30&nbsp;mg/L activation band</strong>. Within that range, the water often becomes\n            <strong>visibly clearer</strong> and more <strong>electrically coherent</strong>, with a softer, more organized feel.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!--\n  REPLIT / MOTION LAYOUT PROMPT – WHAT IT IS\n  - Layout:\n    - Three feature cards in a row on desktop; stacked on mobile.\n  - Motion:\n    - `scroll-fade-up-stagger` for `.andara-grid__item`.\n    - Light `hover-lift-soft` on each card.\n  - Visual:\n    - Optional icons:\n      - Volcanic rock for origin.\n      - Droplet/ion symbol for ionic transformation.\n      - Micro-dropper icon for micro-dosing.\n  -->\n\n  <!-- =========================\n       SECTION – FROM VOLCANO TO GLASS\n  ========================== -->\n  <section\n    id="andara-ionic-journey"\n    class="andara-section andara-section--journey"\n    aria-label="From volcano to glass journey"\n  >\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <header class="andara-section__header">\n        <h2 class="andara-section__headline">\n          From Volcano to Glass – The Andara Journey\n        </h2>\n        <p class="andara-section__subline">\n          <span class="andara-text-lead">\n            To understand Andara Ionic, it helps to see its path as a simple, clear chain of transformations.\n          </span>\n          From <strong>rock</strong> to <strong>ionic sulfate concentrate</strong> to\n          <strong>activated drinking water</strong>, each step is designed to preserve the\n          <strong>elemental richness</strong> while refining the <strong>form</strong>.\n        </p>\n      </header>\n\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--steps andara-section__items">\n        <article class="andara-grid__item andara-grid__item--step">\n          <div class="andara-grid__step-number">1</div>\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            Volcanic Mineral Selection\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Start with carefully selected <strong>volcanic mineral sources</strong> carrying deep-crust signatures –\n            high in <strong>iron, magnesium, calcium, aluminum, silica</strong> and trace elements.  \n            Origin, purity, and consistency are key.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item andara-grid__item--step">\n          <div class="andara-grid__step-number">2</div>\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            Conversion into Ionic Sulfates\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            These minerals are processed into a <strong>clear ionic sulfate solution</strong>.\n            Solid lattice structures are broken down and reorganized as <strong>dissolved ions</strong> that remain stable\n            in liquid form and can directly interact with water’s charge system.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item andara-grid__item--step">\n          <div class="andara-grid__step-number">3</div>\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            Micro-Dose into Your Water\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            A small dose (for example <strong>1&nbsp;ml per 1&nbsp;L</strong>) is added to your water source,\n            calibrated to <strong>17–30&nbsp;mg/L sulfate</strong>. In this range, the water typically\n            <strong>clarifies, reorganizes, and stabilizes</strong> in its charge behaviour.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item andara-grid__item--step">\n          <div class="andara-grid__step-number">4</div>\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            Clarified &amp; Structured Water\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Suspended particles flocculate and settle, <strong>metals and impurities precipitate</strong>, and the\n            remaining water moves toward a <strong>cleaner, more structured state</strong>, often perceived\n            as smoother, softer, and more vital.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!--\n  REPLIT / MOTION LAYOUT PROMPT – JOURNEY\n  - Layout:\n    - Four-step horizontal journey on desktop (1–4), vertical timeline on mobile.\n  - Motion:\n    - Use `scroll-fade-up-stagger` with numbers 1–4.\n    - Optional connecting line with `ambient-flow-line` (subtle line that lights up as user scrolls).\n  - Visual:\n    - Icons: volcano, beaker, dropper, glass of clear water.\n    - This section should feel like a simple storyboard.\n  -->\n\n  <!-- =========================\n       SECTION – HOW IT WORKS IN WATER\n  ========================== -->\n  <section\n    id="andara-ionic-activation"\n    class="andara-section andara-section--activation"\n    aria-label="How Andara Ionic works in water"\n  >\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <header class="andara-section__header">\n        <h2 class="andara-section__headline">\n          What Happens When Andara Ionic Meets Water\n        </h2>\n        <p class="andara-section__subline">\n          <span class="andara-text-lead">\n            When the ionic sulfates enter water, they don’t just “add minerals” – they reorganize the water environment itself.\n          </span>\n          In the <strong>Andara activation range</strong> of roughly <strong>17–30&nbsp;mg/L sulfate</strong>,\n          three key processes come into focus: <strong>flocculation, charge re-balancing, and structured hydration layers</strong>.\n        </p>\n      </header>\n\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--02 andara-section__content">\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            1. Flocculation &amp; Clarification\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Multivalent ions like <strong>Fe³⁺, Al³⁺, Mg²⁺, Ca²⁺</strong> in sulfate form act as\n            <strong>bridges</strong> between suspended particles, organic fragments, and colloids.\n            These tiny debris fields begin to <strong>clump together (flocculate)</strong>, becoming heavier and\n            easier to remove or settle out, thus <strong>clarifying the water</strong>.\n          </p>\n\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            2. Charge &amp; Redox Re-Balancing\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            As the ionic sulfate complex spreads through the water, it reshapes the\n            <strong>charge landscape</strong> – influencing <strong>ORP, conductivity, and local proton gradients</strong>.\n            The water tends to move away from chaotic, unstable charge patterns toward a more\n            <strong>coherent redox environment</strong>.\n          </p>\n\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            3. Structured / EZ-Like Zones\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            At specific concentration windows, lab observations (UV-range absorbance, turbidity changes) indicate\n            the emergence of <strong>ordered hydration domains</strong> – water organizing into more\n            <strong>stable, structured layers</strong> around surfaces and solutes, reminiscent of\n            <strong>EZ-like water</strong> described in structured water research.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <aside class="andara-grid__item">\n          <figure class="andara-figure">\n            <div class="andara-figure__visual">\n              <p>\n                [Diagram visual: a sequence of three glasses – 1) cloudy with scattered particles,\n                2) particles clumping and settling, 3) clear water with subtle hexagonal patterns near the glass wall.]\n              </p>\n            </div>\n            <figcaption class="andara-figure__caption">\n              The Andara activation range: impurities flocculate, charge patterns rebalance, and water moves toward a clearer, more structured state.\n            </figcaption>\n          </figure>\n\n          <div class="andara-highlight-box andara-highlight-box--activation">\n            <h4 class="andara-highlight-box__title">\n              Andara Activation Snapshot\n            </h4>\n            <p class="andara-highlight-box__text">\n              <strong>Typical reference dose:</strong><br>\n              1&nbsp;ml Andara Ionic per 1&nbsp;L water  \n              → ~<strong>17–18&nbsp;mg/L sulfate</strong>  \n              → within the Andara <strong>17–30&nbsp;mg/L activation band</strong>.\n            </p>\n            <ul class="andara-highlight-box__list">\n              <li>Water clarity often improves.</li>\n              <li>Suspended solids become easier to filter or settle.</li>\n              <li>Charge and redox behaviour move toward coherence.</li>\n            </ul>\n            <p class="andara-highlight-box__note">\n              Always follow your local guidelines and the\n              <a href="/andara-dilution-calculator">Andara Dilution Calculator</a>\n              for specific applications.\n            </p>\n          </div>\n        </aside>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!--\n  REPLIT / MOTION LAYOUT PROMPT – ACTIVATION\n  - Layout:\n    - Two-column layout; left for explanation, right for diagram + highlight box.\n  - Motion:\n    - Use `scroll-fade-up` on text and diagram.\n    - Apply `ambient-water-ripple` behind the glasses illustration.\n    - Optional `scroll-step-glow`: as user scrolls, highlight the current glass (1 → 2 → 3).\n  - Visual:\n    - Before/after clarity should be obvious but not exaggerated.\n    - Show hexagonal patterns in a subtle, non-cartoon way.\n  -->\n\n  <!-- =========================\n       SECTION – WHY SULFATE & RARE ELEMENTS\n  ========================== -->\n  <section\n    id="andara-ionic-sulfate-rare"\n    class="andara-section andara-section--science-detail"\n    aria-label="Why sulfate and rare elements matter"\n  >\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <header class="andara-section__header">\n        <h2 class="andara-section__headline">\n          Why Sulfate &amp; Rare Elements Are at the Heart of Andara Ionic\n        </h2>\n        <p class="andara-section__subline">\n          <span class="andara-text-lead">\n            Sulfate is the quiet architect behind many of water’s structural and biological behaviours.\n          </span>\n          When paired with <strong>iron, magnesium, calcium, aluminum, silica, and rare-earth elements</strong>,\n          it becomes a powerful driver of <strong>clarification, structuring, and redox management</strong>.\n        </p>\n      </header>\n\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--03 andara-section__items">\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            Sulfate – The Structural Anion\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Sulfate (SO₄²⁻) interacts strongly with water and charged surfaces. In both\n            <strong>drinking water treatment</strong> and <strong>biology</strong>, sulfate-rich regimes are repeatedly\n            associated with <strong>stable gels, hydration layers, and flocculation</strong>.  \n            Andara Ionic places sulfate at the center of its design.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            Multivalent Cations – Bridges &amp; Anchors\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Ions like <strong>Fe³⁺, Al³⁺, Mg²⁺, Ca²⁺</strong> form <strong>bridges</strong> between particles and surfaces.\n            They bind to colloids, organic residues, and charged interfaces, helping\n            <strong>organize and condense</strong> what would otherwise remain diffuse and cloudy.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            Rare &amp; Ultra-Trace Elements – The Fine Tuning\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Volcanic mineral matrices also carry <strong>rare and ultra-trace elements</strong> in minute amounts.\n            while tiny, these can <strong>modulate redox chemistry, enzyme environments, and field behaviour</strong>,\n            acting like fine-tuning knobs in both water and biology.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!--\n  REPLIT / MOTION LAYOUT PROMPT – SULFATE & RARE ELEMENTS\n  - Layout:\n    - Three science cards with icons (sulfate tetrahedron, bridging cations, fine-tuning dial).\n  - Motion:\n    - `scroll-fade-up-stagger` for cards.\n    - Optional `ambient-crystalline-shimmer` on icons.\n  - Visual:\n    - Semi-technical, diagram-like look but still aligned with Andara aesthetics.\n  -->\n\n  <!-- =========================\n       SECTION – USE SCENARIOS\n  ========================== -->\n  <section\n    id="andara-ionic-scenarios"\n    class="andara-section andara-section--scenarios"\n    aria-label="Use scenarios for Andara Ionic"\n  >\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <header class="andara-section__header">\n        <h2 class="andara-section__headline">\n          Where Andara Ionic Fits – Use Scenarios\n        </h2>\n        <p class="andara-section__subline">\n          <span class="andara-text-lead">\n            Andara Ionic is a precision tool for water and fields, not a generic “add some minerals” product.\n          </span>\n          Its primary role is to <strong>clarify, condition, and structure water</strong>\n          within carefully defined micro-dose ranges.\n        </p>\n      </header>\n\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--04 andara-section__items">\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            Home &amp; Personal Water\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Use as a <strong>water conditioning agent</strong> in combination with filtration,\n            to support clearer, smoother drinking water tuned to the Andara activation range.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            Spa, Wellness &amp; Retreats\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Integrate Andara Ionic into <strong>structured water bars, spa rituals, or retreat offerings</strong>,\n            where users can experience the difference between untreated and Andara-conditioned water.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            Research &amp; Lab Use\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Apply Andara Ionic in <strong>experimental setups</strong> exploring\n            turbidity, flocculation, ORP shifts, or structured water phenomena in controlled conditions.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            Soil &amp; Irrigation (Advanced)\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            In advanced projects, explore Andara Ionic as a <strong>water-conditioning step</strong> in irrigation streams\n            where clarification, mineral codes, and bioelectric properties of water matter.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!--\n  REPLIT / MOTION LAYOUT PROMPT – SCENARIOS\n  - Layout:\n    - 4 cards grid (2x2 on desktop, stacked on mobile).\n  - Motion:\n    - `scroll-fade-up-stagger` + `hover-lift-soft`.\n  - Visual:\n    - Icons per scenario (house, spa, lab flask, leaf/field).\n  -->\n\n  <!-- =========================\n       SECTION – SAFETY & BOUNDARIES\n  ========================== -->\n  <section\n    id="andara-ionic-safety"\n    class="andara-section andara-section--safety"\n    aria-label="Safety and boundaries"\n  >\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <header class="andara-section__header">\n        <h2 class="andara-section__headline">\n          Safety, Boundaries &amp; Responsibility\n        </h2>\n        <p class="andara-section__subline">\n          <span class="andara-text-lead">\n            Andara Ionic is designed as a water clarification and conditioning agent.\n          </span>\n          It is <strong>not a medical product</strong> and is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent disease.\n          All usage must follow <strong>local regulations, product guidelines, and common sense</strong>.\n        </p>\n      </header>\n\n      <div class="andara-grid andara-grid--02 andara-section__content">\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            What Andara Ionic Is Not\n          </h3>\n          <ul class="andara-grid__list">\n            <li>Not a pharmaceutical or medical treatment.</li>\n            <li>Not a replacement for filtration or local safety standards.</li>\n            <li>Not a license to drink unsafe or contaminated water.</li>\n          </ul>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            How to Work with It Responsibly\n          </h3>\n          <ul class="andara-grid__list">\n            <li>Always respect <strong>recommended dilution ranges</strong> and application guidelines.</li>\n            <li>Use in combination with <strong>proper filtration</strong> and infrastructure.</li>\n            <li>Consult <strong>local regulations</strong> for any commercial or large-scale use.</li>\n          </ul>\n        </article>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!--\n  REPLIT / MOTION LAYOUT PROMPT – SAFETY\n  - Layout:\n    - Two columns of bullet lists, simple and clear.\n  - Motion:\n    - `scroll-fade-up` only; this section should feel calm and firm.\n  - Visual:\n    - Simple line icons (shield, checklist).\n  -->\n\n  <!-- =========================\n       SECTION – ANDARA LIBRARY FOOTER HOOK\n  ========================== -->\n  <section\n    id="andara-ionic-library-footer"\n    class="andara-section andara-section--library-footer"\n    aria-label="Andara Science Library footer navigation"\n  >\n    <div class="andara-section__inner">\n      <header class="andara-section__header">\n        <h2 class="andara-section__headline">\n          Dive Deeper into the Andara Science Library\n        </h2>\n        <p class="andara-section__subline">\n          To fully understand Andara Ionic, you can explore the pillars it connects:\n          <strong>water science, mineral science, crystalline matrix, bioelectricity, and the terrain model</strong>.\n        </p>\n      </header>\n\n      <div\n        class="andara-grid andara-grid--04 andara-grid--library-footer andara-section__items"\n        aria-label="Andara Library pillar links"\n      >\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            Water Science\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Structured water, EZ domains, pH/ORP/EC, vortexing and more – how Andara Ionic interacts with the\n            <strong>liquid architecture</strong> of life.\n          </p>\n          <p class="andara-grid__link">\n            <a href="/science/water">Explore Water Science →</a>\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            Mineral Science\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Ionic vs colloidal, sulfate chemistry, trace and rare elements, and comparative mineral sources –\n            the <strong>periodic table behind Andara</strong>.\n          </p>\n          <p class="andara-grid__link">\n            <a href="/science/minerals">Explore Mineral Science →</a>\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            Crystalline Matrix\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Tetrahedrons, hexagons, triangular harmonics – how <strong>sacred geometry and crystal lattices</strong>\n            relate to water and mineral fields.\n          </p>\n          <p class="andara-grid__link">\n            <a href="/science/crystalline-matrix">Explore Crystalline Matrix →</a>\n          </p>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class="andara-grid__item">\n          <h3 class="andara-grid__title">\n            Bioelectric Terrain\n          </h3>\n          <p class="andara-grid__text">\n            Ion transport, cell voltage, proton gradients, and the terrain model – how minerals and structured water\n            influence the <strong>bioelectric landscape</strong>.\n          </p>\n          <p class="andara-grid__link">\n            <a href="/science/bioelectric-terrain">Explore Bioelectric Terrain →</a>\n          </p>\n        </article>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!--\n  REPLIT / MOTION LAYOUT PROMPT – LIBRARY FOOTER\n  - Layout:\n    - 4 cards for the main science pillars (Water, Mineral, Crystalline, Bioelectric).\n    - This acts as a reusable “science library footer” component.\n  - Motion:\n    - `scroll-fade-up-stagger`.\n    - `hover-glow-border` for hover state to invite clicks.\n  - Visual:\n    - Icon per pillar (wave, atom, crystal, lightning/field).\n    - Background can be slightly darker with a nebula-like gradient to feel “library / knowledge base”.\n  -->\n\n</main>	{"components": ["andara-page", "andara-hero", "andara-text-lead", "andara-section", "andara-grid", "andara-figure", "andara-highlight-box"], "extractedAt": "2025-12-09T10:48:49.355Z", "layoutSpecs": [{"spec": "Two-column hero: left text (~60%), right product visual (~40%). Stacks on mobile.", "section": "HERO"}, {"spec": "Three feature cards in a row on desktop; stacked on mobile.", "section": "WHAT IT IS"}, {"spec": "Four-step horizontal journey on desktop (1–4), vertical timeline on mobile.", "section": "JOURNEY"}, {"spec": "Two-column layout; left for explanation, right for diagram + highlight box.", "section": "ACTIVATION"}, {"spec": "Three science cards with icons in a row on desktop; stacked on mobile.", "section": "SULFATE & RARE ELEMENTS"}, {"spec": "4 cards grid (2x2 on desktop, stacked on mobile).", "section": "SCENARIOS"}, {"spec": "Two columns of bullet lists, simple and clear.", "section": "SAFETY"}, {"spec": "4 cards for the main science pillars.", "section": "LIBRARY FOOTER"}], "motionSpecs": [{"section": "HERO", "layoutSpec": "Two-column hero: left text (~60%), right product visual (~40%).", "layoutClass": ".andara-hero", "motionItems": [{"preset": "ambient-water-ripple", "trigger": "loop", "targetSelector": ".andara-hero", "targetDescription": "Background under the hero"}, {"preset": "scroll-fade-up-stagger", "trigger": "scroll", "targetSelector": ".andara-hero__headline, .andara-hero__bullets", "targetDescription": "Headline and bullet points"}, {"preset": "crystalline-shimmer-slow", "trigger": "loop", "targetSelector": ".andara-hero__media", "targetDescription": "Product bottle and water glass visual"}], "colorPalette": ["indigo", "turquoise", "gold"], "vibeKeywords": ["precision", "trust", "origin", "volcanic spring", "clean research lab"], "emotionalTone": ["clarity", "awe", "trust"], "responsiveSpec": "Desktop: text left, image right; mobile: stack with text first.", "imageryDescription": "Show actual Andara-style bottle shape if known (dark glass, minimal label). Place clear “before/after” glasses subtly in background: one slightly turbid, one clear and glowing."}, {"section": "WHAT IT IS", "layoutSpec": "Three feature cards in a row on desktop", "layoutClass": ".andara-grid--03", "motionItems": [{"preset": "scroll-fade-up-stagger", "trigger": "scroll", "targetSelector": ".andara-grid__item", "targetDescription": "Grid items/cards"}, {"